# v7.7.3 supply-chain defense — refuse npm package versions published
# less than 7 days ago. Defends against fresh-malicious-release attacks
# (event-stream, ua-parser-js, @ctrl/tinycolor pattern) where an attacker
# publishes a compromised version and waits for CI/dev workstations to
# pull it before the malicious code is flagged.
#
# Source: adopted from qwibitai/nanoclaw v1.2.52 (2026-04-14) per
# reference_nanoclaw_upstream.md Tier 1 adoption list.
#
# Value is minutes. 10080 min = 7 days. Adjust if a legitimate dependency
# ships an urgent security fix and we need to pull it within the window —
# set `--minimum-release-age 0` on the specific install, never globally.
minimum-release-age=10080
